cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing tasks such as equation verification. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) because it proposes a new model architecture for improving the generalization performance of recursive neural networks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) because it involves the use of neural stacks as external memory. Finally, it could also be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) because recursive neural networks have been successfully applied to image and video data.
